h.com/photos/white-house-under-maple-trees-1ddol8rgUH8','photo-1480074568708-e7b720bb3f09','Small house on an autumn’s day. Photo taken by Scott Webb','inherit','open','closed','','photo-1480074568708-e7b720bb3f09','','','2025-03-07 11:03:34','2025-03-07 11:03:34','',20,'http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/photo-1480074568708-e7b720bb3f09.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(84,1,'2025-03-06 16:53:48','2025-03-06 16:53:48','https://unsplash.com/photos/lake-surrounded-by-rocky-mountains-at-daytime-5GtS0qbcU0s','photo-1503751192943-5537c30ba181','Flowers near mountain lake. Photo taken by Jonas Verstuyft','inherit','open','closed','','photo-1503751192943-5537c30ba181','','','2025-03-07 11:03:26','2025-03-07 11:03:26','',14,'http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/photo-1503751192943-5537c30ba181.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(85,1,'2025-03-06 16:54:42','2025-03-06 16:54:42','https://unsplash.com/photos/person-running-on-road-at-daytime-QVD3Xht9txA','photo-1547483238-f400e65ccd56','Running in the mountain. Photo taken by Andrea Leopardi','inherit','open','closed','','photo-1547483238-f400e65ccd56','','','2025-03-07 11:03:19','2025-03-07 11:03:19','',19,'http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/photo-1547483238-f400e65ccd56.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(86,1,'2025-03-06 16:56:01','2025-03-06 16:56:01','','premium_photo-1694475491345-de84a1ee0f22','','inherit','open','closed','','premium_photo-1694475491345-de84a1ee0f22','','','2025-03-07 10:44:06','2025-03-07 10:44:06','',16,'http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/premium_photo-1694475491345-de84a1ee0f22.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(88,1,'2025-03-07 10:05:00','2025-03-07 10:05:00','Weekend athletes often push themselves to the limit during their limited training time, but many overlook the critical recovery period that follows intense physical activity. Sports medicine specialists recommend five key practices: proper hydration beginning immediately after exercise, protein-rich meals within an hour of finishing, contrast therapy alternating between hot and cold treatments, compression garments during rest periods, and quality sleep of at least seven hours.\n\n\"The recovery window isn\'t just about feeling better faster—it\'s when your body actually makes fitness gains,\" explains Dr. Sarah Chen, sports medicine physician at Metro Health Center. \"The micro-tears in muscles need to repair and rebuild stronger, which can\'t happen optimally without proper nutrition, rest, and recovery protocols.\"','Five Essential Recovery Strategies for Weekend Athletes','','publish','open','open','','five-essential-recovery-strategies','','','2025-03-07 11:11:38','2025-03-07 11:11:38','',0,'https://wordpress.org/?p=2',0,'post','',0),(89,1,'2025-03-07 10:10:00','2025-03-07 10:10:00','Cities around the world are competing to attract the growing demographic of location-independent professionals by developing specialized infrastructure and amenities. These \"remote work hubs\" feature high-speed internet throughout public spaces, co-working facilities with flexible membership options, and community programming designed to combat isolation while fostering professional networking.\n\nThe economic impact has been significant for early adopters like Lisbon, Portugal and Medellín, Colombia, where housing developments specifically designed for digital nomads have revitalized formerly struggling neighborhoods. Urban planners note that these cities are experiencing a new kind of growth pattern, where population increases aren\'t necessarily tied to local job markets but rather to quality of life factors and digital connectivity.','Remote Work Hub Cities Redefining Urban Planning','','publish','open','open','','remote-work-hub-cities','','','2025-03-07 11:07:33','2025-03-07 11:07:33','',0,'https://wordpress.org/?p=3',0,'post','',0),(90,1,'2025-03-07 10:15:00','2025-03-07 10:15:00','Artisanal bread making has surged in popularity worldwide, with enrollment in baking courses increasing by over 200% in the past two years. This revival of traditional bread crafting goes beyond sourdough starters that became popular during pandemic lockdowns—enthusiasts are now exploring heritage grains, regional bread varieties, and ancient fermentation techniques that had nearly disappeared from modern kitchens.\n\nProfessional bakers attribute this phenomenon to a growing desire for tactile experiences and traditional skills in an increasingly digital world. \"There\'s something deeply satisfying about transforming simple ingredients into something nourishing through your own hands,\" notes master baker Julian Rossi. \"It connects people to food traditions that span centuries and cross cultures.\"','Traditional Bread Making Experiences a Global Revival','','publish','open','open','','traditional-bread-making-revival','','','2025-03-07 11:01:39','2025-03-07 11:01:39','',0,'https://wordpress.org/?p=4',0,'post','',0),(91,1,'2025-03-07 10:20:00','2025-03-07 10:20:00','The psychological component of athletic performance has moved from the sidelines to center stage, with professional sports teams now employing full-time mental performance specialists. Training regimens for elite athletes increasingly dedicate as much as 30% of total preparation time to psychological aspects including visualization, pressure simulation, and mindfulness practices.\n\nRecent studies demonstrate that these mental training protocols correlate with measurable performance improvements, particularly in high-pressure situations. Athletes who undergo structured mental skills training show reduced cortisol levels during competition and report greater ability to maintain focus during critical moments. Teams that have invested heavily in sports psychology resources have seen significant improvements in late-game performance metrics and overall consistency.','The Mental Game: How Elite Athletes Train Their Minds','','publish','open','open','','mental-game-elite-athletes','','','2025-03-07 11:00:04','2025-03-07 11:00:04','',0,'https://wordpress.org/?p=5',0,'post','',3),(92,1,'2024-03-07 10:25:00','2024-03-07 10:25:00','Microadventures—short, local outdoor experiences that pack excitement into limited timeframes—have become the solution for adventure-seekers with busy schedules. These deliberately small-scale excursions might involve overnight bivouacking on a nearby hill, wild swimming in local waterways, or exploring urban green spaces through new activities like foraging or night hiking.\n\n\"The beauty of microadventures is their accessibility,\" explains outdoor recreation specialist Maya Williams. \"They require minimal planning, equipment, or travel time, yet deliver genuine adventure experiences that break routine and connect people with nature.\" Local tourism boards have begun promoting microadventure routes and resources, recognizing their appeal to residents seeking regular doses of adventure without significant time commitments or environmental impact from long-distance travel.','Microadventures: The New Weekend Escape Trend','','publish','open','open','','microadventures-weekend-escape-trend','','','2025-03-07 10:55:05','2025-03-07 10:55:05','',0,'https://wordpress.org/?p=6',0,'post','',0),(93,1,'2025-02-07 10:30:00','2025-02-07 10:30:00','Urban neighborhoods previously classified as food deserts are experiencing remarkable transformations through community-managed garden initiatives. These collaborative growing spaces have increased access to fresh produce for thousands of residents while creating green spaces that serve multiple community needs, from educational workshops to intergenerational gathering places.\n\nData from municipal health departments shows promising nutritional impacts, with participating households reporting increased vegetable consumption and greater dietary diversity. Beyond food production, these gardens have become catalysts for broader community engagement, with many evolving into hubs