<ul>\n                    <li>Director: Frank Darabont</li>\n                    <li>Starring: Tim Robbins, Morgan Freeman</li>\n                    <li>Genre: Drama</li>\n                    <li>Release Year: 1994</li>\n                    <li>Runtime: 142 minutes</li>\n                </ul>\n\n                <h2>Critical Reception</h2>\n                <p>The Shawshank Redemption is widely regarded as one of the greatest films of all time. It received multiple award nominations and has a strong following among audiences and critics alike.</p>\n            ','The Shawshank Redemption','','trash','closed','closed','','the-shawshank-redemption__trashed','','','2025-04-08 10:31:34','2025-04-08 10:31:34','',0,'https://example.com/movies/?p=401',0,'movies','',0),(402,1,'2025-04-08 10:22:28','2025-04-08 10:22:28','\n                <img src=\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584721246-e3ddf53424a3\" alt=\"Forrest Gump\" />\n                \n                <h2>Overview</h2>\n                <p>Forrest Gump, directed by Robert Zemeckis, is a 1994 American comedy-drama film based on the 1986 novel of the same name by Winston Groom. The story depicts several decades in the life of Forrest Gump, a slow-witted but kind-hearted man from Alabama who witnesses and unwittingly influences several historical events in the 20th century United States.</p>\n\n                <h2>Key Features</h2>\n                <ul>\n                    <li>Director: Robert Zemeckis</li>\n                    <li>Starring: Tom Hanks, Robin Wright</li>\n                    <li>Genre: Comedy-Drama</li>\n                    <li>Release Year: 1994</li>\n                    <li>Runtime: 142 minutes</li>\n                </ul>\n\n                <h2>Critical Reception</h2>\n                <p>Forrest Gump was a massive commercial success and received widespread acclaim for its performances, particularly Tom Hanks\'s. It won six Academy Awards, including Best Picture, Best Director, and Best Actor for Tom Hanks.</p>\n            ','Forrest Gump','','trash','closed','closed','','forrest-gump__trashed','','','2025-04-08 10:31:34','2025-04-08 10:31:34','',0,'https://example.com/movies/?p=402',0,'movies','',0),(403,1,'2025-04-08 10:22:28','2025-04-08 10:22:28','\n                <img src=\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584721246-e3ddf53424a3\" alt=\"Finding Nemo\" />\n                \n                <h2>Overview</h2>\n                <p>Finding Nemo, directed by Andrew Stanton, is a 2003 American computer-animated adventure film produced by Pixar Animation Studios and released by Walt Disney Pictures. The film tells the story of Marlin, a clownfish, who searches for his missing son, Nemo, who has been captured and placed in a fish tank in a dentist\'s office in Sydney.</p>\n\n                <h2>Key Features</h2>\n                <ul>\n                    <li>Director: Andrew Stanton</li>\n                    <li>Starring: Albert Brooks, Ellen DeGeneres</li>\n                    <li>Genre: Animation, Adventure, Family</li>\n                    <li>Release Year: 2003</li>\n                    <li>Runtime: 100 minutes</li>\n                </ul>\n\n                <h2>Critical Reception</h2>\n                <p>Finding Nemo received universal acclaim and won the Academy Award for Best Animated Feature. It is praised for its storyline, voice acting, and visual appeal.</p>\n            ','Finding Nemo','','trash','closed','closed','','finding-nemo__trashed','','','2025-04-08 10:31:34','2025-04-08 10:31:34','',0,'https://example.com/movies/?p=403',0,'movies','',0),(404,1,'2025-04-08 10:22:28','2025-04-08 10:22:28','\n                <img src=\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584721246-e3ddf53424a3\" alt=\"The Lion King\" />\n                \n                <h2>Overview</h2>\n                <p>The Lion King is a 1994 American animated musical drama film produced by Walt Disney Feature Animation. The story takes place in a kingdom of lions in Africa and was influenced by William Shakespeare\'s Hamlet. It follows the journey of Simba, a young lion who is to succeed his father as King of the Pride Lands, but after his father is murdered by his uncle, Simba is manipulated into thinking he was responsible and flees into exile.</p>\n\n                <h2>Key Features</h2>\n                <ul>\n                    <li>Director: Roger Allers, Rob Minkoff</li>\n                    <li>Starring: Matthew Broderick, James Earl Jones</li>\n                    <li>Genre: Animation, Musical, Drama</li>\n                    <li>Release Year: 1994</li>\n                    <li>Runtime: 88 minutes</li>\n                </ul>\n\n                <h2>Critical Reception</h2>\n                <p>The Lion King was praised for its music, story, and animation. It won two Academy Awards for its achievement in music and the Golden Globe Award for Best Motion Picture – Musical or Comedy.</p>\n            ','The Lion King','','trash','closed','closed','','the-lion-king__trashed','','','2025-04-08 10:31:34','2025-04-08 10:31:34','',0,'https://example.com/movies/?p=404',0,'movies','',0),(405,1,'2025-04-08 10:22:28','2025-04-08 10:22:28','\n                <img src=\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584721246-e3ddf53424a3\" alt=\"Up\" />\n                \n                <h2>Overview</h2>\n                <p>Up, directed by Pete Docter, is a 2009 American computer-animated comedy-drama adventure film produced by Pixar Animation Studios and released by Walt Disney Pictures. The film centers on an elderly widower named Carl Fredricksen and an earnest young boy named Russell. By tying thousands of balloons to his house, Carl sets out to fulfill his dream to see the wilds of South America and complete a promise made to his late wife, Ellie.</p>\n\n                <h2>Key Features</h2>\n                <ul>\n                    <li>Director: Pete Docter</li>\n                    <li>Starring: Edward Asner, Jordan Nagai</li>\n                    <li>Genre: Animation, Adventure, Comedy-Drama</li>\n                    <li>Release Year: 2009</li>\n                    <li>Runtime: 96 minutes</li>\n                </ul>\n\n                <h2>Critical Reception</h2>\n                <p>Up received universal acclaim, particularly for its story, characters, and visuals. It won two Academy Awards, including Best Animated Feature, and was nominated for three others, including Best Picture.</p>\n            ','Up','','trash','closed','closed','','up__trashed','','','2025-04-08 10:31:34','2025-04-08 10:31:34','',0,'https://example.com/movies/?p=405',0,'movies','',0),(406,1,'2025-04-08 10:35:20','2025-04-08 10:35:20','http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/movies-import.xml_.txt','movies-import.xml_.txt','','private','open','closed','','movies-import-xml_-txt','','','2025-04-08 10:35:20','2025-04-08 10:35:20','',0,'http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/movies-import.xml_.txt',0,'attachment','',0),(408,1,'2025-04-08 10:32:59','2025-04-08 10:32:59','<h2>Overview</h2>\nThe Shawshank Redemption, released in 1994, is a drama film based on Stephen King\'s novella \"Rita Hayworth and Shawshank Redemption\". Directed by Frank Darabont, it stars Tim Robbins as Andy Dufresne and Morgan Freeman as Ellis \"Red\" Redding.\n<h2>Plot Summary</h2>\nThe film tells the story of Andy Dufresne, a man sentenced to life in Shawshank State Penitentiary for the murder of his wife and her lover, despite his claims of innocence. Over the years, he forms a friendship with Red, experiences brutality of prison life, adapts, helps the warden, and ultimately gains redemption.\n<h2>Accolades</h2>\nNominated for seven Academy Awards, including Best Picture and Best Actor for Freeman. It has since gained a large cult following and is often regarded as one of the greatest films ever made.','The Shawshank Redemption','Two imprisoned men bond over a number of years, finding solace and eventual redemption through acts of common decency.','publish','closed','closed','','the-shawshank-redemption','','','2025-04-08 10:38:04','2025-04-08 10:38:04','',0,'https://example.com/movies/?p=401',0,'movies','',0),(409,1,'2025-04-08 10:32:59','2025-04-08 10:32:59','<h2>Overview</h2>\nThe Godfather, released in 1972, is a crime film directed by Francis Ford Coppola and based on Mario Puzo\'s best-selling novel of the same name. It stars Marlon Brando, Al Pacino, and James Caan.\n<h2>Plot Summary</h2>\nThe story follows the powerful Italian-American crime family of Don Vito Corleone. When the don\'s youngest son, Michael, reluctantly joins the Mafia, he becomes involved in the inevitable cycle of violence and betrayal.\n<h2>Accolades</h2>\nWon three Academy Awards, including Best Picture, Best Actor for Brando, and Best Adapted Screenplay. It is widely regarded as one of the greatest films in world cinema.','The Godfather','The aging patriarch of an organized crime dynasty transfers control of his clandestine empire to his reluctant son.','publish','closed','closed','','the-godfather','','','2025-04-08 10:38:16','2025-04-08 10:38:16','',0,'https://example.com/movies/?p=402',0,'movies','',0),(410,1,'2025-04-08 10:32:59','2025-04-08 10:32:59','<h2>Overview</h2>\nThe Dark Knight, released in 2008, is a superhero film directed by Christopher Nolan. It stars Christian Bale as Bruce Wayne/Batman, Heath Ledger as the Joker, and Aaron Eckhart as Harvey Dent/Two-Face.\n<h2>Plot Summary</h2>\nBatman, with the help of allies, Gordon and Harvey Dent, sets out to dismantle the remaining criminal organizations that plague Gotham. The triumvirate proves effective, but soon find themselves prey to a reign of chaos unleashed by a rising criminal mastermind known as the Joker.\n<h2>Accolades</h2>\nWon two Academy Awards, including Best Supporting Actor for Ledger. It is widely considered one of the greatest superhero films of all time.','The Dark Knight','When the menace known as the Joker emerges from his mysterious past, he wreaks havoc and chaos on the people of Gotham.','publish','closed','closed','','the-dark-knight','','','2025-04-08 10:38:27','2025-04-08 10:38:27','',0,'https://example.com/movies/?p=403',0,'movies','',0),(411,1,'2025-04-08 10:32:59','2025-04-08 10:32:59','<h2>Overview</h2>\nPulp Fiction, released in 1994, is a crime film directed by Quentin Tarantino. It stars John Travolta, Uma Thurman, and Samuel L. Jackson.\n<h2>Plot Summary</h2>\nThe film\'s narrative is told out of chronological order and follows several storylines involving crime, violence, and redemption. Its eclectic dialogue, ironic mix of humor and violence, and a host of cinematic allusions and pop culture references have established it as a cult classic.\n<h2>Accolades</h2>\nWon the Palme d\'Or at the 1994 Cannes Film Festival and an Academy Award for Best Original Screenplay. It is widely regarded as one of the greatest films of all time.','Pulp Fiction','The lives of two mob hitmen, a boxer, a gangster\'s wife, and a pair of diner bandits intertwine in four tales of violence and redemption.','publish','closed','closed','','pulp-fiction','','','2025-04-08 10:38:38','2025-04-08 10:38:38','',0,'https://example.com/movies/?p=404',0,'movies','',0),(412,1,'2025-04-08 10:32:59','2025-04-08 10:32:59','<h2>Overview</h2>\nSchindler\'s List, released in 1993, is a historical drama film directed and co-produced by Steven Spielberg. It stars Liam Neeson as Oskar Schindler, Ralph Fiennes as Amon Göth, and Ben Kingsley as Itzhak Stern.\n<h2>Plot Summary</h2>\nThe film follows the true story of Oskar Schindler, a German businessman who saved the lives of more than a thousand Polish Jews during the Holocaust by employing them in his factories.\n<h2>Accolades</h2>\nWon seven Academy Awards, including Best Picture, Best Director, and Best Adapted Screenplay. It is widely regarded as one of the most significant films ever made.','Schindler\'s List','In German-occupied Poland during World War II, Oskar Schindler gradually becomes concerned for his Jewish workforce after witnessing their persecution by the Nazis.','publish','closed','closed','','schindlers-list','','','2025-04-08 10:38:53','2025-04-08 10:38:53','',0,'https://example.com/movies/?p=405',0,'movies','',0),(413,1,'2025-04-08 10:32:59','2025-04-08 10:32:59','<h2>Overview</h2>\nForrest Gump, released in 1994, is a comedy-drama film directed by Robert Zemeckis. It stars Tom Hanks, Robin Wright, and Gary Sinise.\n<h2>Plot Summary</h2>\nThe film chronicles several decades in the life of Forrest Gump, a slow-witted but kind-hearted man from Alabama who witnesses and unwittingly influences several historical events in the 20th century United States.\n<h2>Accolades</h2>\nWon six Academy Awards, including Best Picture, Best Director, and Best Actor for Hanks. It is widely regarded as an American classic.','Forrest Gump','The presidencies of Kennedy and Johnson, the Vietnam War, the Watergate scandal and other historical events unfold from the perspective of an Alabama man with an IQ of 75.','publish','closed','closed','','forrest-gump','','','2025-04-08 10:39:07','2025-04-08 10:39:07','',0,'https://example.com/movies/?p=406',0,'movies','',0),(414,1,'2025-04-08 10:32:59','2025-04-08 10:32:59','<h2>Overview</h2>\nInception, released in 2010, is a sci-fi thriller film written and directed by Christopher Nolan. It stars Leonardo DiCaprio, Joseph Gordon-Levitt, and Ellen Page.\n<h2>Plot Summary</h2>\nThe film follows Dom Cobb, a professional thief who steals information by infiltrating the subconscious of his targets. He is offered a chance to have his criminal history erased if he can successfully perform an inception, the planting of an idea into someone\'s subconscious.\n<h2>Accolades</h2>\nWon four Academy Awards, including Best Cinematography and Best Visual Effects. It is widely regarded as one of the greatest sci-fi films of the 21st century.','Inception','A thief who steals corporate secrets through the use of dream-sharing technology is given the inverse task of planting an idea into the mind of a CEO.','publish','closed','closed','','inception','','','2025-04-08 10:39:21','2025-04-08 10:39:21','',0,'https://example.com/movies/?p=407',0,'movies','',0),(415,1,'2025-04-08 10:32:59','2025-04-08 10:32:59','<h2>Overview</h2>\nThe Matrix, released in 1999, is a sci-fi action film written and directed by the Wachowskis. It stars Keanu Reeves, Laurence Fishburne, and Carrie-Anne Moss.\n<h2>Plot Summary</h2>\nThe film depicts a dystopian future in which humanity is unknowingly trapped inside a simulated reality, the Matrix, created by intelligent machines to distract humans while using their bodies as an energy source. Computer programmer Neo learns this truth and is drawn into a rebellion against the machines.\n<h2>Accolades</h2>\nWon four Academy Awards, including Best Visual Effects and Best Film Editing. It is considered a groundbreaking work in the sci-fi genre.','The Matrix','A computer hacker learns from mysterious rebels about the true nature of his reality and his role in the war against its controllers.','publish','closed','closed','','the-matrix','','','2025-04-08 10:39:32','2025-04-08 10:39:32','',0,'https://example.com/movies/?p=408',0,'movies','',0);
